Turtle is a library that emulates the LOGO environment.
The user controls a little turtle that carries a pen. By moving and turning the turtle, one can create tons of crazy drawings.
## Coordinates
The turtle world is centered on a portrait screen. x coordinates go from left to right and y coordinates go from bottom to top.
## Initialization
Make sure to call `initialize portrait` or `initialize landscape` once before calling any other turtle command. It prepares the turtle environment.
## Seeing the moves
The turtle moves fast but you can slow it down by using `slow motion`.
## Moving
Use `forward` to move the turtle forward.
To go backwards, use a negative distance.
## Turning
You can turn the turtle left (counter clockwise) or right (clockwise) by a certain amount of degrees.
You can also use negative angles.
## Customizing the pen
You can change the color of the pen
You can change the thickness of the pen.
## Pen up, pen down
You can lift and put down the pen. When the pen is lifted, the turtle does not draw anything when moving.
## Circles
It is possible to draw circle efficiently using the `circle` action.
Creates a landscape turtle environment
Sets the duration of each step in seconds.
Adds a little pause between each step
